      • getExtraData

        public static org.json.JSONObject getExtraData(android.content.Context context,
                               PwAlertExtras extras)
                                        throws com.phunware.core.exceptions.PwException

        Get extra data associated with an Alert using it's associated PID. This only needs to be called if extra data is expected.

        Parameters:
        context - a context to work with
        extras - Alert Extras that were received.
        Returns:
        A JSONObject is returned if extra data exists
        Throws:
        com.phunware.core.exceptions.PwException - Thrown if there is an error:
        • For a network error.
        • No internet connection.
        • No data found.

      • onMessage

        public abstract void onMessage(android.content.Context context,
             PwAlertExtras extras)

        Called when an alert is received. The only interaction that this SDK has before this point (and after GCM) is that the intent object received from GCM is parsed into a PwAlertExtras object.

        If extra data is expected in the alert then get the PID from the alert extras object:
        String pid = extras.getDataPID();
        and call the method getExtraData(android.content.Context, PwAlertExtras)

        Parameters:
        context - Current application context.
        extras - The extras that were parsed from GCM.
